  "title": "defining max in a RangeSlider automatically filters results to that max value",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nDefining max in a RangeSlider automatically filters results to that max value\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAll results to come in until the user actually filters them.\r\n\r\n## 🖥 Screenshots\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4541410/160559876-7f6185b7-f3cd-4cdf-b168-0ba7ff7ee295.png)\r\n\r\n## Additional context\r\n\r\n```\r\nrangeSlider({\r\n    container: '#price-range-slider',\r\n    attribute: 'price',\r\n    max:8000,\r\n  }),\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nAdding the filter automatically is a nice future to have in some scenarios. The default should be to work with all results until the end user actually interacts with the widget.   The way instantsearch works now how do I go about removing that max filter optimaly?\r\n\r\n",
